Twenty phenolic compounds were classified as phloroglucinols with an attached monoterpene or sesquiterpene moiety. Their identification was based upon the combination of UV absorbance at 277 nm, comparison of measured and theoretical monoisotopic mass within < ± 2 ppm error and the presence of the diagnostic MS/MS fragments (
 Table 1) (
 Eschler et al., 2000; 
 Singh and Bharate, 2006; 
 Santos et al., 2019).
